article.headline: Tulsa 84, Colorado 59
article.story: TULSA, Okla. -- Justin Hurtt scored 21 points as Tulsa remained unbeaten at home with an 84-59 victory over Colorado on Saturday. Jerome Jordan had 14 points and eight rebounds, Steven Idlet 12 points and 11 rebounds and Ben Uzoh 13 points and seven assists for Tulsa (10-3). Alec Burks led Colorado (8-5) with 17 points, and Cory Higgins had 13. The Buffaloes have lost 21 consecutive road games against Division I schools. Tulsa, which is 10-0 at Reynolds Center, led 36-29 at halftime. Hurtt had three 3-pointers and a dunk as the Golden Hurricane widened the lead to 62-44 with 10:27 remaining.
